This kernel is the same as the kernel-huge from slackware.
It just have the following additions:
- aufs2 filesystem supportÂ : http://aufs.sourceforge.net/
- lzma compression support for squashfs, patched by Cyrille Pontvieux based on the patch by Phillip Lougher:
  * http://marc.info/?l=linux-fsdevel&m=126049544600760&w=2
  * http://marc.info/?l=linux-kernel&m=126282556400666&w=2
  * http://marc.info/?l=linux-kernel&m=126049538900666&w=2
  * http://marc.info/?l=linux-fsdevel&m=126049544400738&w=2
I also used the following patches for making it work for 2.6.36 after reading it myself to approve the patch (it's better than not reading):
http://chakra-project.org/sources/kernel26/patch-2.6.36-3-CHAKRA.bz2

Lougher messages on LKML: http://marc.info/?a=103594540500001&r=1&w=2
